Global sales continue quite strong with U.S. sales YTD higher but not as strong
as non-us growth. This could be due to the lower dollar making non-us products
more price competitive. Gross margins increased to 46% up from 43% and their
international markets show solid high 25% growth YTD.

Management continues to reinvent their supply chain and inventory management
systems. This helps the company maintain their high margins and allows quick
new product introduction. Once the manufacturing of the Altec Lansing products
are folded into this new system and product manufacturing is moved to China,
profitability should follow.

Based on their forward PE of 18, PLT may still be a value proposition given
their performance in their communication division worldwide. The sleeper asset
is their Altec Lansing division. The stock sold in the $35 area but fell down
below $20 when management reported their first quarter results (after their
buyout in April 2006) of their Altic Lansing division.

The company has the opportunity to capitalize on their purchase of the Altec
Lansing assets and they are more than half way completing their turnaround.
That's why I plan to continue to hold at least for another 6-8 months.

EKS
