Date:7/27/2007 7:29:32 PM
From:E_K_S
Hi Jurgis - I have bookmarked your homebuilder selection Meritage Homes
Corporation (MTH). I still think the company can trade lower and I will wait
for a buy entry around $17.00. I am familiar with Nevada real estate and
recently homes that sold for $620,000 are now selling at $490,000. After
listening to their conference call they confirm this as MTH was seeing the
largest declines in Nevada off 74% this year. California was off more than 53%
but Texas was doing good.

Looking at the balance sheet the company has a strong balance sheet but debt to
equity is misleading as the company has been marking down their current
inventory. Book Value decreases as their mark downs continue but at some point
their market inventory value will stabilize and the value investor will be
better able to evaluate the value of their hard assets.

Since MTH operates in many of the markets that are of interest to me and seem
to be an efficient builder, this might be one to watch when the market turns. I
think it is still too early to buy in the current cycle, this may be a good one
to own when the time is right.

